What types of problems are solved with virtualization? 
 Virtualizations can prevent downtime and data loss from servers and it can even lower costs for companies because it helps them perform the same tasks using fewer physical servers
 
 What role does hypervisor play in virtualization? 
  Hypervisors take your physical resources and divide them up so that virtual environments can use them.
   Hypervisors take your physical resources and divide them up so that virtual environments can use them.
    Virtual machines function as a single data finle that can be moved from a computer to another and expected to work the same.
   
   In your own words explain the difference between cloud computing and virtualization expanding on your analysis in the prior module. 

   The main concept of cloud computing is the remote use of applications and features that are commonly used on a computer over the internet.
Both data storage and server processing can be done from anywhere, everything being available on virtual servers. 

Virtualizaton is used to create a virtual infrastructure on a physical device.
It is a solution that enables you to run more than one operating system and different applications simultaneously on the same machine.
Cloud computing allows users to access information from another location using the internet and Virtualizatoin Creates a new virtual machine inside a physical computer.
